
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-tschofenig-ace-oauth-bt-01.txt'>
    <title>"The OAuth 2.0 Bearer Token Usage over the Constrained Application Protocol (CoAP)", Hannes Tschofenig</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-tschofenig-ace-oauth-bt-01.txt</link>
    <description>This specification describes how to use OAuth 2.0 bearer tokens to access protected resources using the Constrained Application Protocol (CoAP).  Any party in possession of a bearer token (a "bearer") can use it to get access to the associated resources (without demonstrating possession of a cryptographic key).  To prevent misuse, bearer tokens need to be protected from disclosure in storage and in transport.</description>
    <dc:date>2015-03-08T08:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
